340 g Pork Chops, boneless
2 unit(s) Flatbread
2 unit(s) Russet Potato
1 unit(s) Shallot
1 unit(s) Tomato
28 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Greek Yogurt
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
4 g Dill-Garlic Spice Blend
1.33 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F. Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes, half the Zesty Garlic Blend and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven 12-14 min, until golden on one side. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Peel, then cut shallot into 1/2-inch slices.
Pat pork dry with paper towels. Season with half the Dill-Garlic Spice Blend, remaining Zesty Garlic Blend, salt and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted for 12-14 min, remove from oven.
Flip potatoes and gather on one side of the baking sheet.
To the other side of the baking sheet, beside potatoes, add shallots. Top shallots with pork chops. Drizzle 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil over top. (Note: For 4 servings, split shallots and pork chops between both baking sheets.)
Roast in the middle of the oven 12-16 min until veggies are tender and pork is cooked through.** (Note: For 4 servings, rotate sheets halfway through.)

To a medium bowl, add yogurt, feta and remaining Dill-Garlic Spice Blend. Stir to combine.

When pork and veggies are almost done, place flatbreads directly on the top oven rack.
Toast for 2-3 min, until softened. (Note: If you do not want toasted flatbread, skip this step.)

Thinly slice pork.
Arrange flatbreads on a clean surface.
Spread some of the feta spread over one side of flatbreads.
On the other side of flatbreads, stack spring mix, shallots, pork and tomatoes.
Divide wraps and potatoes between plates.
Serve remaining feta spread alongside for dipping.